[SN]TITLE[SN]
Bridgend A4106 crash: Tributes to teenager killed by car

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A teenager killed after being hit by a car in Bridgend was "a young man just starting out in the world", his family have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Deividas Andrijauskas, 19, was critically injured when a car mounted a kerb on the A4106 Tythegston road at about 16:00 BST on Friday 7 October.
The aspiring DJ, from Wildmill in Bridgend, died in hospital on Wednesday morning.
His family said his death had left a "massive hole" in their family.
In a statement his family described him as "caring, loving and full of life and energy" who was "always smiling".
"He went out that day to visit friends and we had no idea that he would never come home," their statement said.
A second pedestrian was taken to Princess of Wales Hospital in Bridgend following the incident.
South Wales Police are appealing for witnesses to the collision.
